refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public boolImagick::borderImage mixedbordercolor intwidth intheight
Surrounds the image with a border of the color defined by the bordercolor ImagickPixel object.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     PECL imagick 2.1.0

      Now allows a string representing the color as the first parameter.
      Previous versions allow only an ImagickPixel object.

  &reftitle.examples;



       Imagick::borderImage


<?php
function borderImage($imagePath, $color, $width, $height) {
    $imagick = new \Imagick(realpath($imagePath));
    $imagick->borderImage($color, $width, $height);
    header("Content-Type: image/jpg");
    echo $imagick->getImageBlob();
}

?>
